{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01YHhfAqHRDWXjXL4qYVLX2i","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 8-1: Rust Stack and App Type Detection\n     2→\n     3→## Status: backlog\n     4→\n     5→## Story\n     6→\n     7→As a developer initializing codeharness on a Rust project,\n     8→I want the harness to detect my project as Rust and identify whether it's a CLI, server, library, or agent,\n     9→So that all downstream features (coverage, OTLP, Dockerfile) use the correct Rust configuration.\n    10→\n    11→## Acceptance Criteria\n    12→\n    13→- [ ] AC1: Given a directory contains `Cargo.toml`, when `detectStack()` is called, then it returns `'rust'` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    14→- [ ] AC2: Given a Rust project with `[[bin]]` in Cargo.toml and no web framework deps, when `detectAppType()` is called, then it returns `'cli'` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    15→- [ ] AC3: Given a Rust project with `axum` in `[dependencies]`, when `detectAppType()` is called, then it returns `'server'` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16→- [ ] AC4: Given a Rust project with `[lib]` section and no `[[bin]]`, when `detectAppType()` is called, then it returns `'generic'` (library) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    17→- [ ] AC5: Given a Rust project with `async-openai` in dependencies, when `detectAppType()` is called, then it returns `'agent'` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    18→- [ ] AC6: Given a Rust project with `[workspace]` in Cargo.toml, when `detectStack()` is called, then it still returns `'rust'` (treated as single project) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    19→- [ ] AC7: Given no `Cargo.toml` exists, when `detectStack()` is called, then Rust is NOT detected (no false positive) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    20→\n    21→## Technical Notes\n    22→\n    23→### Stack Detection\n    24→\n    25→File: `src/lib/stack-detect.ts` — `detectStack()` at L7-14.\n    26→\n    27→Add `if (existsSync(join(dir, 'Cargo.toml'))) return 'rust';` after the Python checks. Use existing `readTextSafe()` helper already present in the file for reading Cargo.toml content.\n    28→\n    29→### App Type Detection\n    30→\n    31→File: `src/lib/stack-detect.ts` — `detectAppType()` at L72-145.\n    32→\n    33→Add `if (stack === 'rust') { ... }` block after the Python block (around L142). Implement a `getCargoContent()` helper using `readTextSafe()` to read `Cargo.toml`.\n    34→\n    35→Add these constants at module level:\n    36→```typescript\n    37→const RUST_WEB_FRAMEWORKS = ['actix-web', 'axum', 'rocket', 'tide', 'warp'];\n    38→const RUST_AGENT_DEPS = ['async-openai', 'anthropic', 'llm-chain'];\n    39→```\n    40→\n    41→### Detection Priority Order\n    42→\n    43→1. **Agent**: any dep in `RUST_AGENT_DEPS` found in `[dependencies]` section\n    44→2. **Server**: any dep in `RUST_WEB_FRAMEWORKS` found in `[dependencies]` section\n    45→3. **CLI**: `[[bin]]` section present without web framework deps\n    46→4. **Library**: `[lib]` section present, no `[[bin]]`\n    47→5. **Generic**: fallback\n    48→\n    49→### Cargo.toml Parsing\n    50→\n    51→Use simple string matching — no TOML parser dependency (NFR4). Check for section headers like `[workspace]`, `[[bin]]`, `[lib]`, and search for dependency names in `[dependencies]` section text. `readTextSafe()` is already available in the file.\n    52→\n    53→For `[workspace]` projects, still return the detected app type based on root deps. Workspace is detected but treated as a single project — no per-crate enumeration.\n    54→\n    55→### Tests\n    56→\n    57→File: `src/lib/__tests__/stack-detect.test.ts`\n    58→\n    59→Mirror existing Node.js/Python test patterns. Use `vi.mock('node:fs')` to mock `existsSync` and `readFileSync`. Create Cargo.toml content fixtures for:\n    60→- Plain binary crate (`[[bin]]`)\n    61→- Library crate (`[lib]`)\n    62→- Workspace crate (`[workspace]`)\n    63→- Web framework project (axum in deps)\n    64→- Agent project (async-openai in deps)\n    65→- No Cargo.toml (negative case)\n    66→\n    67→## Files to Change\n    68→\n    69→- `src/lib/stack-detect.ts` — Add Rust branch to `detectStack()` (L11), add `RUST_WEB_FRAMEWORKS` and `RUST_AGENT_DEPS` constants, add Rust block to `detectAppType()` (L142), add `getCargoContent()` helper\n    70→- `src/lib/__tests__/stack-detect.test.ts` — Add Rust test cases for stack detection and all app type variants\n    71→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6b184f1a-3a3f-4307-8da0-d8cf52066851","uuid":"58544e6f-d927-4350-a28c-ce3f1aa8f56c","timestamp":"2026-03-23T05:09:06.243Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/8-1-rust-stack-and-app-type-detection.md","content":"# Story 8-1: Rust Stack and App Type Detection\n\n## Status: backlog\n\n## Story\n\nAs a developer initializing codeharness on a Rust project,\nI want the harness to detect my project as Rust and identify whether it's a CLI, server, library, or agent,\nSo that all downstream features (coverage, OTLP, Dockerfile) use the correct Rust configuration.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC1: Given a directory contains `Cargo.toml`, when `detectStack()` is called, then it returns `'rust'` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n- [ ] AC2: Given a Rust project with `[[bin]]` in Cargo.toml and no web framework deps, when `detectAppType()` is called, then it returns `'cli'` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n- [ ] AC3: Given a Rust project with `axum` in `[dependencies]`, when `detectAppType()` is called, then it returns `'server'` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n- [ ] AC4: Given a Rust project with `[lib]` section and no `[[bin]]`, when `detectAppType()` is called, then it returns `'generic'` (library) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n- [ ] AC5: Given a Rust project with `async-openai` in dependencies, when `detectAppType()` is called, then it returns `'agent'` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n- [ ] AC6: Given a Rust project with `[workspace]` in Cargo.toml, when `detectStack()` is called, then it still returns `'rust'` (treated as single project) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n- [ ] AC7: Given no `Cargo.toml` exists, when `detectStack()` is called, then Rust is NOT detected (no false positive) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n\n## Technical Notes\n\n### Stack Detection\n\nFile: `src/lib/stack-detect.ts` — `detectStack()` at L7-14.\n\nAdd `if (existsSync(join(dir, 'Cargo.toml'))) return 'rust';` after the Python checks. Use existing `readTextSafe()` helper already present in the file for reading Cargo.toml content.\n\n### App Type Detection\n\nFile: `src/lib/stack-detect.ts` — `detectAppType()` at L72-145.\n\nAdd `if (stack === 'rust') { ... }` block after the Python block (around L142). Implement a `getCargoContent()` helper using `readTextSafe()` to read `Cargo.toml`.\n\nAdd these constants at module level:\n```typescript\nconst RUST_WEB_FRAMEWORKS = ['actix-web', 'axum', 'rocket', 'tide', 'warp'];\nconst RUST_AGENT_DEPS = ['async-openai', 'anthropic', 'llm-chain'];\n```\n\n### Detection Priority Order\n\n1. **Agent**: any dep in `RUST_AGENT_DEPS` found in `[dependencies]` section\n2. **Server**: any dep in `RUST_WEB_FRAMEWORKS` found in `[dependencies]` section\n3. **CLI**: `[[bin]]` section present without web framework deps\n4. **Library**: `[lib]` section present, no `[[bin]]`\n5. **Generic**: fallback\n\n### Cargo.toml Parsing\n\nUse simple string matching — no TOML parser dependency (NFR4). Check for section headers like `[workspace]`, `[[bin]]`, `[lib]`, and search for dependency names in `[dependencies]` section text. `readTextSafe()` is already available in the file.\n\nFor `[workspace]` projects, still return the detected app type based on root deps. Workspace is detected but treated as a single project — no per-crate enumeration.\n\n### Tests\n\nFile: `src/lib/__tests__/stack-detect.test.ts`\n\nMirror existing Node.js/Python test patterns. Use `vi.mock('node:fs')` to mock `existsSync` and `readFileSync`. Create Cargo.toml content fixtures for:\n- Plain binary crate (`[[bin]]`)\n- Library crate (`[lib]`)\n- Workspace crate (`[workspace]`)\n- Web framework project (axum in deps)\n- Agent project (async-openai in deps)\n- No Cargo.toml (negative case)\n\n## Files to Change\n\n- `src/lib/stack-detect.ts` — Add Rust branch to `detectStack()` (L11), add `RUST_WEB_FRAMEWORKS` and `RUST_AGENT_DEPS` constants, add Rust block to `detectAppType()` (L142), add `getCargoContent()` helper\n- `src/lib/__tests__/stack-detect.test.ts` — Add Rust test cases for stack detection and all app type variants\n","numLines":71,"startLine":1,"totalLines":71}}}
