{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013ZH6iVFgn9VESqKktFsWpr","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→title: 'Full Rust Stack Support'\n     3→slug: 'rust-stack-support'\n     4→created: '2026-03-23'\n     5→status: 'ready-for-dev'\n     6→stepsCompleted: [1, 2, 3, 4]\n     7→tech_stack: ['typescript', 'rust', 'vitest', 'semgrep']\n     8→files_to_modify:\n     9→  - src/lib/stack-detect.ts\n    10→  - src/lib/otlp.ts\n    11→  - src/lib/coverage.ts\n    12→  - src/lib/state.ts\n    13→  - src/modules/infra/dockerfile-template.ts\n    14→  - src/modules/infra/docs-scaffold.ts\n    15→  - src/commands/init.ts\n    16→  - src/modules/infra/init-project.ts\n    17→  - src/modules/observability/analyzer.ts\n    18→  - src/lib/deps.ts\n    19→files_to_create:\n    20→  - templates/otlp/rust.md\n    21→  - templates/Dockerfile.verify.rust\n    22→  - patches/observability/rust-function-no-tracing.yaml\n    23→  - patches/observability/rust-catch-without-tracing.yaml\n    24→  - patches/observability/rust-error-path-no-tracing.yaml\n    25→code_patterns:\n    26→  - 'if/else on stack === \"nodejs\" | \"python\" — add \"rust\" branch at each'\n    27→  - 'Per-stack install/patch/detect functions: installNodeOtlp(), installPythonOtlp() → add installRustOtlp()'\n    28→  - 'Cargo.toml TOML parsing for app type and dependency detection'\n    29→test_patterns:\n    30→  - 'Mirror existing stack-detect.test.ts patterns for Rust cases'\n    31→  - 'Mirror otlp.test.ts patterns with Cargo.toml fixtures'\n    32→  - 'Mirror coverage.test.ts patterns with tarpaulin JSON fixtures'\n    33→---\n    34→\n    35→# Tech-Spec: Full Rust Stack Support\n    36→\n    37→**Created:** 2026-03-23\n    38→\n    39→## Overview\n    40→\n    41→### Problem Statement\n    42→\n    43→Codeharness supports Node.js and Python across stack detection, OTLP instrumentation, coverage tools, Dockerfile generation, Semgrep rules, and docs scaffolding. Rust projects get `null` stack and no harness features. ~25 language-conditional code paths need Rust branches.\n    44→\n    45→### Solution\n    46→\n    47→Add Rust as a first-class stack at parity with TypeScript/Python. Use `cargo-tarpaulin` for coverage, `opentelemetry`/`opentelemetry-otlp` crates for OTLP, basic scaffolding + LLM guidance for instrumentation, and Semgrep Rust rules for observability static analysis. Treat workspaces (`[workspace]`) as single projects.\n    48→\n    49→### Scope\n    50→\n    51→**In Scope:**\n    52→- Stack detection (`Cargo.toml`, `[workspace]` support)\n    53→- App type detection (CLI/library/server via Cargo.toml parsing)\n    54→- Dockerfile generation (`rustTemplate()`)\n    55→- Verification Dockerfile (`Dockerfile.verify.rust`)\n    56→- OTLP dependency addition + config + LLM guidance docs\n    57→- Coverage tool detection (`cargo-tarpaulin`)\n    58→- Coverage report parsing (tarpaulin JSON format)\n    59→- Semgrep rules for Rust observability patterns\n    60→- Docs scaffolding (AGENTS.md, build commands)\n    61→- State file support (`rust` stack, `cargo-tarpaulin` tool)\n    62→- Tests for all new code paths\n    63→\n    64→**Out of Scope:**\n    65→- Full auto-instrumentation code generation (LLM handles this via guidance docs)\n    66→- Per-crate workspace enumeration (treat workspace as single project)\n    67→- New observability backends\n    68→- Custom verification strategies\n    69→\n    70→## Context for Development\n    71→\n    72→### Codebase Patterns\n    73→\n    74→- All stack-conditional logic uses `if (stack === 'nodejs') { ... } else if (stack === 'python') { ... }` — add `else if (stack === 'rust') { ... }` at each location\n    75→- Per-stack functions follow naming convention: `installNodeOtlp()`, `installPythonOtlp()` → add `installRustOtlp()`\n    76→- Coverage detection follows: `detectNodeCoverageTool()`, `detectPythonCoverageTool()` → add `detectRustCoverageTool()`\n    77→- Dockerfile templates follow: `nodejsTemplate()`, `pythonTemplate()` → add `rustTemplate()`\n    78→- OTLP templates are static markdown files in `templates/otlp/{stack}.md`\n    79→- Tests mirror source structure: `src/lib/__tests__/`, `src/modules/infra/__tests__/`\n    80→\n    81→### Files to Reference\n    82→\n    83→| File | Purpose | Lines | Rust Touchpoints |\n    84→| ---- | ------- | ----- | ---------------- |\n    85→| `src/lib/stack-detect.ts` | Stack detection + app type detection | 146 | `detectStack()` L7-14, `detectAppType()` L72-145, add Rust dep constants |\n    86→| `src/lib/otlp.ts` | OTLP instrumentation per stack | ~330 | `installRustOtlp()` new fn, `instrumentProject()` L295, `configureOtlpEnvVars()` L258-274, `configureAgent()` L207-227 |\n    87→| `src/lib/coverage.ts` | Coverage tool detection + report parsing | ~400 | `detectCoverageTool()` L35-53, `detectRustCoverageTool()` new fn, `parseTarpaulinCoverage()` new fn, `parseCoverageReport()` L257, `parseTestCounts()` L308 add cargo test format, `CoverageToolInfo.tool` type union |\n    88→| `src/lib/state.ts` | HarnessState interface | — | `coverage.tool` type, `otlp.rust_env_hint` field |\n    89→| `src/modules/infra/dockerfile-template.ts` | Dockerfile generation per stack | 119 | `rustTemplate()` new fn, `generateDockerfileTemplate()` L99-108 |\n    90→| `src/modules/infra/docs-scaffold.ts` | AGENTS.md + docs generation | 197 | `getStackLabel()` L32-36, `getCoverageTool()` L38-41, `generateAgentsMdContent()` L43-98 |\n    91→| `src/modules/observability/analyzer.ts` | Semgrep static analysis runner | ~150 | No code changes — Semgrep auto-discovers `.yaml` rules by language |\n    92→| `src/lib/deps.ts` | Dependency registry | ~100 | Add `cargo-tarpaulin` to `DEPENDENCY_REGISTRY` |\n    93→| `patches/observability/*.yaml` | Semgrep rules (JS/TS) | 3 files | Create 3 new Rust-specific YAML rules |\n    94→| `templates/otlp/nodejs.md` | Node.js OTLP guide | 54 | Pattern for `templates/otlp/rust.md` |\n    95→| `templates/otlp/python.md` | Python OTLP guide | 52 | Pattern for `templates/otlp/rust.md` |\n    96→| `templates/Dockerfile.verify` | Node.js verification Dockerfile | — | Pattern for `templates/Dockerfile.verify.rust` |\n    97→\n    98→### Technical Decisions\n    99→\n   100→- **Cargo.toml parsing:** Use `readTextSafe()` (already in stack-detect.ts) + simple string matching / regex on TOML content. No TOML parser dependency. Check for `[workspace]`, `[[bin]]`, `[lib]`, and known framework deps in `[dependencies]`."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01UrsWACEgNx3cQjKftiWn4D","session_id":"6b184f1a-3a3f-4307-8da0-d8cf52066851","uuid":"8cd325c1-490f-4909-baea-46afd44d38d0","timestamp":"2026-03-23T05:12:09.080Z"}
